Sadie and Maud BY GWENDOLYN BROOKS Maud went to college. Sadie stayed at home. Sadie scraped life With a fine-tooth comb.
She didn’t leave a tangle in. Her comb found every strand. Sadie was one of the livingest chits In all the land.
Sadie bore two babies Under her maiden name. Maud and Ma and Papa Nearly&hellip;
